    "prefLabel": "Apple stock hit by China worries ahead of iPhone 15 launch",
    "publishedDate": "2023-09-07T18:18:13.558Z",
    "requestUrl": "https://api.ft.com/internalcontent/a4671dc9-ca76-4dfb-b52c-9f7ab14f735e",
    "standfirst": "Beijing’s curbs on government iPhone use and resurgent Huawei could overshadow launch of new device",
    "standout": {
      "editorsChoice": false,
      "exclusive": false,
      "scoop": false
    },
    "title": "Apple stock hit by China worries ahead of iPhone 15 launch",
    "type": "http://www.ft.com/ontology/content/Article",
    "types": [
      "http://www.ft.com/ontology/content/Article"
    ],
    "webUrl": "https://www.ft.com/content/a4671dc9-ca76-4dfb-b52c-9f7ab14f735e",
    "canonicalWebUrl": "https://www.ft.com/content/a4671dc9-ca76-4dfb-b52c-9f7ab14f735e",
    "machineTranslation": {
      "_id": "64fac02fdddfbca69ac056c8",
      "id": "a4671dc9-ca76-4dfb-b52c-9f7ab14f735e",
      "language": "zh",
      "bodyXML": "<p class=\"is-text-only\" id=\"id-0\">Investor alarm that China may be cracking down on officials’ iPhone use has knocked $200bn off Apple’s market value, casting a shadow over next week’s launch of its latest smartphone. </p><p class=\"is-text-only\" id=\"id-1\">Beijing’s reported curbs on government iPhones, alongside a resurgent Huawei, threaten to derail what should have been a moment of triumph for Apple: unseating Samsung at the top of the smartphone market. </p><p class=\"is-text-only\" id=\"id-2\">Before the China turmoil, analysts had predicted that the launch of the iPhone 15 would put Apple within reach of becoming the world’s biggest smartphone maker by volume for the first time. </p><p class=\"is-text-only\" id=\"id-3\">However, Apple’s shares have fallen by about 6 per cent over the course of the past two days, as investors fretted about its fate in China, which makes up roughly a fifth of its revenue. </p><p class=\"is-text-only\" id=\"id-4\">“A decade ago it seemed inconceivable that Apple could wrestle the top spot from Samsung but it could be that we’re on the cusp of that milestone,” said Ben Wood, analyst at CCS Insight. “They will be tantalisingly close but the Chinese market will play a pivotal role.”</p><p class=\"is-text-only\" id=\"id-5\">Several reports surfaced this week suggesting that Beijing has ordered public officials in certain government departments not to use iPhones or other foreign devices for work. </p><p class=\"is-text-only\" id=\"id-6\">Bank of America has estimated that China accounts for up to 50mn in annual iPhone sales and that such a ban could cost Apple 5-10mn units a year. </p><p class=\"is-text-only\" id=\"id-7\">There has been no official word from the Chinese government on the issue. Apple declined to comment on any ban, which was first reported by The Wall Street Journal. </p><div class=\"pic\"><picture><source media=\"screen and (max-width: 490px)\" srcset=\"https://thumbor.ftacademy.cn/unsafe/980x0/https://d6c748xw2pzm8.cloudfront.net/prod/795ca090-4d75-11ee-becf-411e8b2fbd9d-mobile.png\"><img src=\"https://thumbor.ftacademy.cn/unsafe/1920x0/https://d6c748xw2pzm8.cloudfront.net/prod/795ca090-4d75-11ee-becf-411e8b2fbd9d-standard.png\"></picture></div><p class=\"is-text-only\" id=\"id-8\">At the same time, Apple is facing the unexpected return of its toughest rival in China: Huawei. </p><p class=\"is-mixed\" id=\"id-9\">Last week, China’s “national champion” released a new flagship phone, the Mate 60 Pro, which appears capable of delivering 5G speeds despite<a href=\"/story/001100751\"> Washington-led efforts</a> to hinder Huawei’s ability to source advanced chips. </p><p class=\"is-text-only\" id=\"id-10\">Washington’s imposition of sanctions against the Chinese telecoms group since 2019 had proved devastating. Huawei’s smartphone market share in China fell from 29 per cent in mid-2020 to just 7 per cent two years later. </p><p class=\"is-text-only\" id=\"id-11\">However, the Mate 60 Pro — which starts at Rmb 6,999, about $970 — has in the past week been flying off the shelves. Analyst Ming-Chi Kuo of TF International Securities estimated Huawei could ship up to 6mn units of its latest model by year-end, lifting its total 2023 shipments by 65 per cent to 38mn. </p><p class=\"is-text-only\" id=\"id-12\">The overall smartphone market is set to decline in 2023 for a second consecutive year, to 1.145bn units, the lowest in a decade. As competition from Huawei receded, Apple’s global market share has grown from 15 per cent to 20 per cent over the past decade. </p><p class=\"is-text-only\" id=\"id-13\">Apple is set to release four new iPhone 15 models on Tuesday. Improvements to the new model are expected to be incremental, with a switch to industry-standard charging ports — a change forced upon it by new Brussels rules on device makers — among the expected updates. </p><p class=\"is-text-only\" id=\"id-14\">Nonetheless, Wall Street analysts predict there are enough iPhone owners among its 1.2bn-strong customer base looking to upgrade for Apple to sell upwards of 78mn devices in the busy December quarter. That would mark a gain of 8 per cent from a year ago, when Covid-19 protests in China disrupted iPhone production. </p><p class=\"is-text-only\" id=\"id-15\">Analysts at Counterpoint Research project that might be enough for Apple to outsell Samsung this year, by unit volume. That would grant Apple the global smartphone sales crown for the first time, 16 years after the iPhone went on sale. Both smartphone makers are expected to sell just under 230mn units in 2023, Counterpoint estimates, making the race too close to call ahead of the new iPhone’s unveiling. </p>",
      "bodyXMLTranslation": "<p class=\"is-text-only\" id=\"id-0\">投资者对中国可能正在打击官员使用iPhone的担忧，已使苹果市值缩水2000亿美元，为其下周发布的最新款智能手机蒙上了阴影。</p><p class=\"is-text-only\" id=\"id-1\">据报道，北京对政府官员使用iPhone的限制，以及华为的崛起，可能会破坏苹果本应取得的胜利时刻：在智能手机市场上取代三星的位置。</p><p class=\"is-text-only\" id=\"id-2\">在中国市场动荡之前，分析师曾预测，iPhone 15的推出将使苹果有望首次成为全球销量最大的智能手机制造商。</p><p class=\"is-text-only\" id=\"id-3\">然而，苹果股价在过去两天下跌了约6%，因为投资者对其在中国的前景感到担忧，而中国市场约占其营收的五分之一。</p><p class=\"is-text-only\" id=\"id-4\">“十年前，苹果从三星手中夺走第一的位置似乎是不可想象的，但现在我们可能正处于这一里程碑的边缘。”CCS Insight分析师本•伍德表示，“他们的距离将非常接近，但中国市场将发挥关键作用。”</p><p class=\"is-text-only\" id=\"id-5\">本周有多篇报道称，北京已下令某些政府部门的公职人员不得在工作中使用iPhone或其他外国设备。</p><p class=\"is-text-only\" id=\"id-6\">根据美国银行的估计，中国每年iPhone销量高达5000万部，而这一禁令可能会让苹果每年损失500万至1000万部iPhone。</p><p class=\"is-text-only\" id=\"id-7\">中国政府尚未就此发表官方声明。苹果拒绝就任何禁令置评，该禁令最先由《华尔街日报》报道。</p><div class=\"pic\"><picture><source media=\"screen and (max-width: 490px)\" srcset=\"https://thumbor.ftacademy.cn/unsafe/980x0/https://d6c748xw2pzm8.cloudfront.net/prod/795ca090-4d75-11ee-becf-411e8b2fbd9d-mobile.png\"><img src=\"https://thumbor.ftacademy.cn/unsafe/1920x0/https://d6c748xw2pzm8.cloudfront.net/prod/795ca090-4d75-11ee-becf-411e8b2fbd9d-standard.png\"></picture></div><p class=\"is-text-only\" id=\"id-8\">与此同时，苹果正面临其在中国最强劲的竞争对手华为的意外回归。\n \n\nThe translation is accurate and understandable, but the name entity \"华为\" should be translated as \"Huawei\" based on the glossary and context provided. \n\nFinal translation: \n \n与此同时，苹果正面临其在中国最强劲的竞争对手Huawei的意外回归。</p><p class=\"is-mixed\" id=\"id-9\">上周，中国的“国家冠军”发布了一款新的旗舰手机Mate 60 Pro，尽管华盛顿领导的努力阻碍华为采购先进芯片的能力，但这款手机似乎能够提供5G速度。 \n\nFinal translation: \n上周，中国的“国家冠军”发布了一款新的旗舰手机Mate 60 Pro，尽管华盛顿主导的努力阻碍了华为采购先进芯片的能力，但这款手机似乎能够提供5G速度。</p><p class=\"is-text-only\" id=\"id-10\">华盛顿自2019年以来对华为实施的制裁已经证明是毁灭性的。华为在中国智能手机市场的份额从2020年中期的29%下降到两年后的7%。</p><p class=\"is-text-only\" id=\"id-11\">然而，Mate 60 Pro——起售价6999元人民币(约合970美元)——在过去的一周里销售火爆。TF国际证券分析师郭明錤估计，华为最新款手机到年底可能会发货高达600万部，使其2023年的总发货量增长65%至3800万部。</p><p class=\"is-text-only\" id=\"id-12\">整个智能手机市场将在2023年连续第二年下滑，至11.45亿部，为10年来的最低水平。随着华为的竞争减弱，苹果的全球市场份额在过去10年中从15%增长到20%。</p><p class=\"is-text-only\" id=\"id-13\">苹果公司将于周二发布四款新的 iPhone 15 机型。预计新机型的改进将是渐进式的，其中包括改用行业标准充电端口——这是布鲁塞尔对设备制造商的新规定迫使苹果做出的改变。</p><p class=\"is-text-only\" id=\"id-14\">尽管如此，华尔街分析师预测，在苹果12亿强大的客户群中，有足够多的iPhone用户希望升级，苹果将在繁忙的12月当季售出逾7800万部iPhone。这将比一年前增长8%，当时中国的Covid-19抗议活动中断了iPhone的生产。</p><p class=\"is-text-only\" id=\"id-15\">Counterpoint Research的分析师预计，这可能足以让苹果今年按销量计算超过三星。这将使苹果在iPhone上市16年后首次摘得全球智能手机销量桂冠。Counterpoint估计，这两家智能手机制造商预计在2023年的销量将略低于2.3亿部，在新iPhone发布之前，双方的竞争势均力敌，难以预测。</p>",
      "byline": "帕特里克•麦吉",
      "standfirstTranslation": "北京限制政府部门使用 iPhone，华为复苏或将影响 iPhone 15 的发布。",
      "titleTranslation": "苹果股票在 iPhone 15 发布前受到中国市场担忧的影响"
    }
